  "en_snotes_asad": "Lit., \"We could surely have effaced their eyes\": a metaphor for \"We could have created them morally blind\" and, thus, devoid of all sense of moral responsibility - which, in its turn, would constitute a negation of all spiritual value in human life as such. (Cf. 2:20 - \"if God so willed, He could indeed take away their hearing and their sight\".) In this instance - as, e.g., in 20:96 - the verb basura (\"he became seeing\" or \"he saw\") is obviously used in its tropical sense of \"perceiving [somethingj mentally\". According to Ibn Abbas, as quoted by Tabari, the phrase anna yubsirun signifies \"how could they perceive the truth\".",
